<DATE>05/25/2009</DATE>
<AUTHOR>rcizme</AUTHOR>
<TEXT>Although some call it an SUV it's not. I don't drive it off road and don't plan to but on snow covered mountain roads it out handles my 4x4 Explorer in every way. The SH-AWD is one of the best I've ever driven. On performance, I didn't buy it as a race car but I drive over a mountain pass to work every day and this car doesn't work very hard climbing the grade AND with just over 50K miles, I'm averaging 24 MPG. I'm confused as to why so many complain about poor fuel economy. I'm guessing that mileage figures vary with driving habits? It's not a race car... don't drive it like one.</TEXT>
<FAVORITE>Premium sound system, Blue tooth, SH-AWD</FAVORITE>
